.fed-2.base.curriculum
  .container.span8
  
    .curriculum-overview
      h2 Front End Curriculum Overview
      p We believe that like writing, syntax is the easy part of front end development. The emphasis of our class is how to <em>think like an engineer</em>. Programming is a lifelong study, and our goal is for you to learn how to learn. 
      p That being said, you'll leave our class with a toolbox of skills that will set you far apart from other junior-level programmers. You'll cover an incredible amount of ground in 3 months, learning everything below and then some. Some topics like Backbone.js will take weeks to cover, others topics like JavaScript templates will be covered over just a few lectures. No matter your learning pace, we work with each student individually to make sure no one falls behind. 
      
      .columns
        
        ul.left-column
          li.expandable 
            | Git and GitHub
            ul
              li Branching, merging, committing, etc.
              li Workflows for teams in GitHub
          li HTML
          li.expandable 
            | CSS
            ul
              li Layouts
              li Typography
              li Interactions
              li CSS3 animations
          li.expandable 
            | Preprocessors
            ul
              li Haml
              li Slim
              li Sass
              li Compass
          li Responsive CSS / media queries
          li Design fundamentals
        
        ul.center-column
          li.expandable 
            | JavaScript
            ul
              li Types
              li Functions
              li Objects
              li Scope
              li Closures
              li Constructors
              li Prototypes
              li JSON
          li.expandable 
            | jQuery
            ul
              li DOM manipulation
              li Non-DOM methods ($.extend, $.proxy, etc)
              li Chaining
              li Callbacks
              li AJAX
              li jQuery plugins
          li.expandable 
            | Underscore.js
            ul
              li Underscore basics
              li Functional programming principles using undersocre
          li.expandable 
            | Backbone.js
            ul
              li Models, collections, views, routers
              li Handling JSON payloads
              li Data persistence with the server
              li Smart management of views
          li.expandable 
            | JavaScript Testing
            ul
              li Jasmine
              li QUnit
          li CoffeeScript
          li.expandable
            | JavaScript Templating
            ul
              li Undersocre.js templates
              li Skim templates
          li Ruby 101
        
        ul.right-column
          li.expandable 
            | Rails Basics
            ul
              li Creating a new Rails app
              li Ruby-flavored MVC
              li Interfacing with external APIs like Twitter, Instagram, etc.
          li Heroku Deployment with Git
          li Parse as a Backend
          li.expandable 
            | Front End Package Managers, Tools, Asset Loaders, and Generators
